 A Catholic priest kidnapped in Enugu State has been freed, officials have said. Theophilus Ndulue, the Parish Priest of St. Patrick Ihuonyia, Amansi-Odo, Ezeagu Local Government Area, Enugu State, was abducted on Friday. The reverend father was kidnapped on his way back from the Diocesan Pastoral Council meeting held at Holy Ghost Cathedral, Enugu. The Enugu State Police Public Relations Officer, Ebere Amaraizu, who confirmed the priestâ€™s release, said he was released unhurt. Also confirming his release, the Director of Communications, Catholic Diocese of Enugu, Benjamin Achi, thanked God that Ndulue returned safe and sound. He prayed God to expose the perpetrators to forestall future occurrence.